      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-cou1",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under flow conditions spanning 2–8 L/min and 2000–3500 RPM, fully encompassing the CPB operating envelope. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity matched to plasma at 37°C) used in experiments. Geometric similarity confirmed. Validation activities are assessed as directly relevant to COU1 operating conditions and device class."
